SIMPLE: intrenchment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intrenchment
<hw>In*trench"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Intrench</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of intrenching or the state of being
intrenched.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>Any defensive work consisting of
at least a trench or ditch and a parapet made from the earth thrown up
in making such a ditch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On our side, we have thrown up <qex>intrenchments</qex> on Winter
and Prospect Hills.</q> <rj><qau>Washington.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Any defense or protection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An encroachment or infringement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The slight <qex>intrenchment</qex> upon individual freedom.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intrepid</ent>⟦br⟧
